  "text": "To test if the extent or time course of fusion pore expansion is modulated by PKC activation, the time course of electrical conductance for individual fusion pores connecting the intragranular lumen to the extracellular space was calculated from the C m trace. The resulting increase in pore conductance was approximated by fitting a straight line as previously described [CITATION_1] . The slope of this line indicates the rate, r, of the conductance increase in [CITATION_2] ). nS/s. For C m steps Ͻ50 fF, the time course of fusion pore conductance was not well resolved. Therefore, only C m steps Ͼ50 fF were used for the fusion pore analysis. For steps Ͼ50 fF, the measured pore expansion rates were not correlated with the step sizes (data not shown; [CITATION_3] .",
